  "why": "The paper applies mutations in a continuous, learned style/latent space (the MUNIT style space) and synthesises images by decoding those continuous style vectors via the GAN decoder (G2). The authors describe encoding environmental conditions as high-dimensional style vectors and searching that style space for critical vectors, then generating test images as x2 = G2(c1, s2). Nowhere in the paper do the authors state that they enforce input-format constraints (e.g., clipping/rounding to integer pixel ranges) or that they generate or save images in a particular serialized format (PNG/JPEG) to ensure perturbations survive serialization. Because the perturbations are produced via continuous latent/style manipulations and there is no explicit handling of serialization/format constraints described, this corresponds to mutating in a continuous intermediate representation without enforcing relevant format constraints, which matches the \"Low\" level in the metric definition.",
